在中立國視察小組撤離後，[[北韓|朝鮮]]方面便認為中立國監察委員會僅是一個有名無實的機構。<ref name="S/2008/547">{{Cite report|url = http://www.securitycouncilreport.org/atf/cf/%7B65BFCF9B-6D27-4E9C-8CD3-CF6E4FF96FF9%7D/NKorea%20S2008547.pdf|title = Detailed report by the Panmunjom Mission of the Korean People's Army|author = Permanent Representative of the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea to the United Nations|id = S/2008/547|publisher = United Nations Security Council|date = 12 August 2008|accessdate = 3 May 2013}}</ref>1970年，一份[[美國|美國]]軍備控制與裁軍署（Arms Control and Disarmament Agency）的報告中稱中立國監察委員會的存在目的即是「為了監督[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国|朝]][[大韩民国|韓]]兩國對[[朝鲜停战协定|停戰協定]]第13條(c)項及第13條(d)項等規定的履行；而該規定既已失其效力，委員會本身亦已無存續的理由」。<ref name="ACDA/WEC/FO69-65">{{Cite report|url = http://oldsite.nautilus.org/DPRKBriefingBook/armistice/NeutralNationsSpervisoryCommission1970.pdf|title = The Neutral Nations Supervisory Commission in Korea|id = ACDA/WEC/FO 69-65|publisher = U.S. Arms Control and Disarmament Agency|oclc = 50820200|date = August 1970|accessdate = 3 May 2013}}</ref>

中立國監察委員會內的歷史學家如此形容這樣的情況：
{{quotation|[[美國|美國]]及[[韓國|韓國]]將不再受[[捷克斯洛伐克|捷克斯洛伐克]]和[[波蘭|波蘭]]的牽制，並可以自由地加速兩國聯軍武裝的現代化；兩國現在更可以從容地革除先前不斷造成阻礙的各種不便，甚至有能力反制[[朝鮮|朝鮮]]和[[中國|中國]]可能用於對抗韓美兩國的政治宣傳手段。中立國監察委員會現在成為一種象徵，其持續存在的目的僅是為了消除無人監督或調停的恐懼。<ref name=ACDA/WEC/FO69-65 />}}
自1956年6月開始到1996年為止，監察委員會雖然已失去對雙方的控制，但其依然持續將參戰國的軍事人員人數報告彙整予[[軍事停戰委員會|軍事停戰委員會]]。委員會中[[波蘭|波蘭]]、[[捷克斯洛伐克|捷克]]、[[瑞典|瑞典]]及[[瑞士|瑞士]]的代表團人數皆在逐漸減少：1956年6月9日已減少至每國14名成員，1960年代減少至每國9名成員，1978年時更減至每國僅6名成員。

[[瑞典|瑞典]]及[[瑞士|瑞士]]委員及其工作人員的營區位於[[朝韩非军事区|朝鮮非軍事區]]的南端，並與[[共同警备区|共同警備區]]毗鄰。[[波蘭|波蘭]]及[[捷克斯洛伐克|捷克]]的原本位於[[三八线|軍事停戰線]]以北的營區目前已被[[朝鮮人民軍|朝鮮人民軍]]收回，並用於其他用途。

在[[东欧剧变|東歐巨變]]後，[[捷克斯洛伐克|捷克斯洛伐克]]及[[波蘭|波蘭]]相繼加入[[北大西洋公約組織|北大西洋公約組織]]；隨後於1993年的[[天鵝絨分離|天鵝絨分離]]中，[[捷克斯洛伐克|捷克斯洛伐克]]分裂為[[捷克共和國|捷克共和國]]以及[[斯洛伐克|斯洛伐克共和國]]。這一連串的事件使[[北韓|朝鮮]]認為中立國監察委員已失去其公正性及中立性，並進一步宣稱該委員會已不存在。<ref name="S/2008/547">{{Cite report|url = http://www.securitycouncilreport.org/atf/cf/%7B65BFCF9B-6D27-4E9C-8CD3-CF6E4FF96FF9%7D/NKorea%20S2008547.pdf|title = Detailed report by the Panmunjom Mission of the Korean People's Army|author = Permanent Representative of the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea to the United Nations|id = S/2008/547|publisher = United Nations Security Council|date = 12 August 2008|accessdate = 3 May 2013}}</ref>[[北韓|朝鮮]]於1993年驅逐了[[捷克|捷克]]委員。隨後於1995年，[[波蘭|波蘭]]委員亦被驅逐。<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1995/Polish-Observers-Leave-North-Korea-Via-Beijing/id-5510aaf2b70c87d82d3de04f3969ee1c|title = Polish Observers Leave North Korea Via Beijing|agency = Associated Press|date = 9 March 1995|accessdate = 4 May 2013|quote = A group of six Polish military observers arrived in Beijing today after North Korea expelled them from their posts near the heavily fortified Korean Demilitarized Zone. ... Poland, along with Czechoslovakia, had represented the North's interests on an international committee overseeing the armistice. But Pyongyang no longer views the former Communist nations as allies now that they are democracies. Czechoslovakia withdrew under pressure in 1993.}}</ref><ref name="yearbook-1995">{{Cite book|page = 460|url = https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=KkrKoVFA7QwC|title = Asian Yearbook of International Law 1995|author = Ko Swan Sik, M. C. W. Pinto, J. J. G. Syatauw|publisher = Martinus Nijhoff Publishers|year = 1997|isbn = 9789041103758}}</ref>

自1995年起，[[北韓|朝鮮]]便不再承認中立國監察委員會的存在。<ref name="yearbook-1995">{{Cite book|page = 460|url = https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=KkrKoVFA7QwC|title = Asian Yearbook of International Law 1995|author = Ko Swan Sik, M. C. W. Pinto, J. J. G. Syatauw|publisher = Martinus Nijhoff Publishers|year = 1997|isbn = 9789041103758}}</ref>[[瑞典|瑞典]]及[[瑞士|瑞士]]委員則持續將[[韓國軍隊|韓國軍隊]]人數的報告送交[[北韓|朝鮮]]，而[[北韓|朝鮮]]方面則悉數予以忽略。<ref name="stripes-20100203">{{Cite news|url = http://www.stripes.com/news/uncollected-paperwork-a-sign-of-dmz-battle-of-wills-1.98578|title = Uncollected paperwork a sign of DMZ battle of wills|author = Jon Rabiroff|newspaper = Stars and Stripes|date = 3 February 2010|accessdate = 3 May 2013}}</ref>即便無法繼續監看[[朝鲜人民军|朝鮮軍隊]]的動態，[[波蘭|波蘭]]委員仍持續出席監察委員會的會議。<ref>{{Cite news|last1 = Kim|first1 = Eun-jung|title = Poland promises to continue armistice monitoring mission|url = http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/fullstory/2013/07/27/73/4500000000AEN20130727002100320F.HTML|accessdate = 3 January 2015|agency = Yonhap|date = 27 July 2013|quote = Although Poland no longer has its delegation in the communist nation, Kupiecki said his country remains committed to fulfilling its mission to oversee the armistice. Now, Poland sends representatives to a couple of commission meetings through South Korea each year.}}</ref>

